02/09/2007
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Serbian President Boris Tadic announced on Saturday (September 1st) that he will run in the next presidential elections. 
Tadic, chairman of Serbia's Democratic Party (DS), said that with the help of coalition partners, he will be able to implement the development plan he intends to present shortly. 
According to Tadic, the national development plan will be in line with similar projects in EU member nations. 
The DS "will never give up the European pathway of Serbia, and Serbia should be a member of the EU at the end of that road," Tadic said. 
(Tanjug, RTRS, B92, Beta - 01/09/07)
